<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880511-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Tech-Sym Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TSY </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Mason Best Co., a Dallas investment firm, said it raised its stake in Houston-based Tech-Sym Corp. to 5.1%.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Mason Best said it holds 336,900 Tech-Sym common shares, including 8,000 bought last Wednesday for $12.625 each.    Mason Best said its decision on future holdings would depend on factors including &quot;evaluation of the need to acquire additional shares to control or to influence the affairs&quot; of Tech-Sym. It said added shares would be acquired in the open market, in private transactions, by a negotiated merger or other business combination, or by a tender offer for all or some of the company's shares outstanding.    In Dallas, a Mason Best spokesman declined to comment on the company's investment in the defense electronics concern.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Tech-Sym's shares closed at $12.25, up 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>